{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "%matplotlib inline\n",
    "import scipy.linalg as scl\n",
    "\n",
    "import pyemma.coordinates as pco\n",
    "import pyemma.msm as pmsm\n",
    "import pyemma.plots as mplt\n",
    "\n",
    "from msmtools.analysis.dense.pcca import _pcca_connected_isa"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "In this notebook, we will apply EDMD algorithm to analyze a diffusion in a two-well potential\n",
    "$$ \\mathrm{d}X_t = - V'(X_t) \\mathrm{d}t + \\sigma(X_t) \\mathrm{d}W_t $$\n",
    "$$ V(x) = (x^2 - 1)^2. $$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Simulation and Evolution of Densities\n",
    "Let's repeat what we did for the previous example: we set up the numerical integrator, and then have a look at the evolution of probability distributions with time."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Euler scheme for gradient flow SDE:\n",
    "def Euler_Scheme(x0, sigma, dt, m, dV):\n",
    "    # Prepare output:\n",
    "    y = np.zeros(m)\n",
    "    y[0] = x0\n",
    "    # Initialize at x0:\n",
    "    x = x0\n",
    "    # Integrate:\n",
    "    for kk in range(1, m):\n",
    "        # Update:\n",
    "        xn = x - dV(x) * dt + np.sqrt(dt) * sigma * np.random.randn(1)\n",
    "        # Update current state:\n",
    "        y[kk] = xn\n",
    "        x = xn\n",
    "    return y"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Use the above function to produce 1000 simulations, each comprising discrete 100 steps, at integration time step 1e-2, starting from uniformly drawn initial conditions in $[-1.5, 1.5]$. Produce a histogram of the data after $[5, 10, 20, 50, 100]$ steps."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Settings:\n",
    "m = 100\n",
    "dt = 1e-2\n",
    "ntraj = 1000\n",
    "\n",
    "# Derivative of the energy:\n",
    "dV = lambda x: 4*x*(x**2 - 1)\n",
    "# Diffusion:\n",
    "sigma = 1.0\n",
    "\n",
    "# Prepare output:\n",
    "X = np.zeros((ntraj, m))\n",
    "for ii in range(ntraj):\n",
    "    #x0 = 1.0\n",
    "    x0 = 3 * np.random.rand(1) - 1.5\n",
    "    X[ii, :] = Euler_Scheme(x0, sigma, dt, m, dV)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "Text(0.5, 1.0, 'Time Evolution of Distribution')"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 5,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Time instances to be used for histogramming:\n",
    "t_vec = np.array([5, 10, 20, 50, 100])\n",
    "# Bins for histogram:\n",
    "xe = np.arange(-2.5, 2.51, 0.1)\n",
    "xc = 0.5 * (xe[1:] + xe[:-1])\n",
    "\n",
    "# Histogram the data at different time instances:\n",
    "plt.figure()\n",
    "\n",
    "qq = 0\n",
    "for t in t_vec:\n",
    "    h, _ = np.histogram(X[:, t-1], bins=xe, density=True)\n",
    "    plt.plot(xc, h, \"--\", linewidth=2.5, label=\"t = %.2f\"%(dt * (t)))\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.xlabel(\"x\", fontsize=12)\n",
    "plt.tick_params(labelsize=12)\n",
    "plt.legend(loc=2)\n",
    "plt.title(\"Time Evolution of Distribution\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Estimating the Koopman Operator"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def koopman_matrix(X, Y, psi, n):\n",
    "    # Get info on data:\n",
    "    m = X.shape[0]\n",
    "    # Evaluate basis set on full data:\n",
    "    PX = np.zeros((n, m))\n",
    "    PY = np.zeros((n, m))\n",
    "    for l in range(m):\n",
    "        PX[:, l] = psi(X[l])\n",
    "        PY[:, l] = psi(Y[l])\n",
    "    # Compute Koopman matrix:\n",
    "    K = np.dot(scl.pinv(PX.T), PY.T)\n",
    "    return K"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Produce 10,000 pairs $(x_l, y_l)$ by drawing $x_l$ from the invariant measure of our SDE. To do so, first draw initial conditions from a uniform distribution in $[-1.5, 1.5]$, and let them equilibrate by running the dynamics for 50 discrete steps. Use the terminal conditions of these simulations as $x_l$. Compute each $y_l$ by running the dynamics again over time $t = 0.1$ (just 10 discrete time steps). \n",
    "\n",
    "Then, estimate the Koopman matrix for a Gaussian basis with equidistant centers in $[-1.2, 1.2]$, with bandwidth $0.5$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Produce the data:\n",
    "m = 10000\n",
    "x = np.zeros(m)\n",
    "y = np.zeros(m)\n",
    "# Generate equilibrated initial conditions:\n",
    "nsteps_cor = 50\n",
    "for l in range(m):\n",
    "    x[l] = Euler_Scheme(3 * np.random.rand(1) - 1.5, sigma, dt, nsteps_cor+1, dV)[-1]\n",
    "# Perform actual simulations:\n",
    "nsteps = 10\n",
    "for l in range(m):\n",
    "    y[l] = Euler_Scheme(x[l], sigma, dt, nsteps+1, dV)[-1]\n",
    "# Define basis set:\n",
    "mu_vec = np.arange(-1.2, 1.21, 0.2)\n",
    "n = mu_vec.shape[0]\n",
    "sig_psi = 0.5\n",
    "psi = lambda x: np.array([np.exp(-0.5*(x - mu_vec[k])**2/(sig_psi**2)) for k in range(n)])\n",
    "# Compute Koopman matrix:\n",
    "K = koopman_matrix(x, y, psi, n)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Compute the first few eigenvalues of the Koopman matrix. Then, use the spectral mapping theorem to projecr eigenvalues at lag times $[0.1, 0.2, ..., 2.0]$."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stderr",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "/Users/fkn1/anaconda3/lib/python3.7/site-packages/numpy/core/numeric.py:538: ComplexWarning: Casting complex values to real discards the imaginary part\n",
      "  return array(a, dtype, copy=False, order=order)\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "Text(0.5, 1.0, 'Eigenvalues predicted by Koopman matrix')"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 8,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Diagonalize K:\n",
    "d, V = scl.eig(K)\n",
    "# Sort eigenvalues and eigenvectors:\n",
    "ind = np.argsort(d)[::-1]\n",
    "d = d[ind]\n",
    "V = V[:, ind]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot eigenvalues at multiple lag times:\n",
    "lags = nsteps * np.arange(1, 21)\n",
    "plt.figure()\n",
    "for k in range(1, 3):\n",
    "    plt.plot(dt*lags, d[k]**(lags / nsteps), \"o\")\n",
    "plt.xlabel(r\"$t$\")\n",
    "plt.ylabel(r\"$\\lambda_k(t)$\")\n",
    "plt.title(\"Eigenvalues predicted by Koopman matrix\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Infer the implied relaxation timescales from the eigenvalues of your Koopman matrix. These are defined as\n",
    "$$ t_k = -\\frac{t}{\\log(\\lambda_k(t))}$$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Implied timescales: \n",
      "[4.53073791-0.j 0.24252613-0.j 0.13155356-0.j 0.08284128-0.j]\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Determine timescales:\n",
    "print(\"Implied timescales: \")\n",
    "its = -(nsteps*dt) / np.log(d[1:5])\n",
    "print(its)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Finding Structure based on the Koopman matrix"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We will now use the Koopman matrix to identify long-lived parts of the state space. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Evaluate the first two eigenfunctions at all data points:\n",
    "PX = np.zeros((n, m))\n",
    "for l in range(m):\n",
    "    PX[:, l] = psi(x[l])\n",
    "VX = np.dot(V[:, :2].T, PX)\n",
    "VX[0, :] = np.mean(VX[0, :])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Apply PCCA:\n",
    "chi, A = _pcca_connected_isa(VX.T, n_clusters=2)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 12,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Evaluate membership functions on a grid:\n",
    "xp = np.arange(-1.5, 1.51, 0.1)\n",
    "pxp = np.zeros((n, xp.shape[0]))\n",
    "for l in range(xp.shape[0]):\n",
    "    pxp[:, l] = psi(xp[l])\n",
    "chi_p = np.dot(A.T, np.dot(V[:, :2].T, pxp))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 13,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "Text(0.5, 1.0, 'Memberships for Macrostates')"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 13,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "for k in range(2):\n",
    "    plt.plot(xp, chi_p[k, :], linewidth=2.5, label=\"State %d\"%k)\n",
    "plt.legend(loc=1)\n",
    "plt.xlabel(\"x\")\n",
    "plt.title(\"Memberships for Macrostates\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": []

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",

    "### Alternative: MSM Construction"
   ]
  },
  {

   "execution_count": 14,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {

      "text/plain": [
       "[<matplotlib.lines.Line2D at 0x7fc677bbe048>]"
      ]

    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Generate a single long simulation:\n",
    "xlong = Euler_Scheme(0.0, sigma, dt, 50000, dV)\n",
    "plt.plot(xlong)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 15,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Assign each time step to a box:\n",
    "dtraj = pco.assign_to_centers(xlong, centers=xc[:, None])"
   ]
  },
  {

   "metadata": {},

    "# Complete implied timescales for a series of lag times:\n",
    "its = pmsm.timescales_msm(dtraj, lags=nsteps * np.arange(1, 21), nits=4)"
